  "prompt": "Which car services are available in Orlando? How good are they compared to taxis and relative to each other?",
  "response": "In Orlando, several car services are available:\n\n1. Rideshare Services:\n- Uber: Widely available, generally affordable, good coverage\n- Lyft: Similar to Uber, competitive pricing\n- Good for convenience and typically cheaper than traditional taxis\n\n2. Traditional Taxi Services:\n- Mears Taxi\n- Orlando Cab Company\n- Generally more expensive than rideshare, less convenient\n\n3. Shuttle Services:\n- Orlando Airport Shuttle\n- SuperShuttle\n- Good for airport transfers, fixed rates\n\n4. Car Services/Limos:\n- Mears Transportation\n- Orlando Transportation\n- More expensive, but offer higher-end vehicles and professional drivers\n\n5. Car Rental Services:\n- Enterprise\n- Hertz\n- Alamo\n- Budget\n- Good for longer stays or extensive city exploration\n\nComparatively:\n- Rideshares (Uber/Lyft) are usually most convenient and cost-effective\n- Traditional taxis are more expensive\n- Shuttle services are good for specific routes\n- Limo services offer premium experiences\n\nRecommendations depend on specific needs like budget, number of passengers, and trip purpose.",
